      "text": "The Air Nomad caves are an ancient cave system located on a mountainside near the Northern Air Temple. They were once frequented by airbenders, who came there to meditate and contemplate the mysteries of life and the universe. By 171 AG, it was used by the Red Lotus as its base to imprison the members of the new Air Nation and hold Avatar Korra before they poisoned her in an attempt to kill her while in the Avatar State."
    },
    {
      "body": "After the Red Lotus captured the airbenders at the Northern Air Temple, they were sent to this cave to be kept as prisoners, guarded by several ${link_0}. After ${link_1} defeated Korra, he tied her up in chains in the sanctuary of the hideout. ${link_2}, managing to escape being captured, found the cave after following the Red Lotus on his ${link_3}, ${link_4}. He led ${link_5}, ${link_6}, ${link_7}, and ${link_8} to the hideout. They defeated the Red Lotus sentries who guarded the airbenders and escaped.",
